{"post_content":"<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Day 1 \u2013 Docker Fundamentals<\/strong><\/h2>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 1: Introduction to Docker<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What is Docker?<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The benefits of containerization<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Docker vs. Virtual Machines<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>How Docker fits into modern software development<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 2: Getting Started with Docker<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Installing Docker<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Understanding Docker architecture (Docker Engine, CLI, Daemon)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>First steps: Running your first container<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Working with images and containers<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 3: Core Docker Commands<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Managing containers: <code>run<\/code>, <code>start<\/code>, <code>stop<\/code>, <code>restart<\/code>, <code>rm<\/code><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Inspecting containers with <code>inspect<\/code>, <code>logs<\/code>, <code>stats<\/code><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Managing images: <code>pull<\/code>, <code>push<\/code>, <code>rmi<\/code>, <code>tag<\/code><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Understanding layers and caching in Docker<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 4: Working with Dockerfiles<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What is a Dockerfile?<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Writing and optimizing Dockerfiles<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Key instructions:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><code>FROM<\/code>, <code>RUN<\/code>, <code>COPY<\/code>, <code>ADD<\/code>, <code>CMD<\/code>, <code>ENTRYPOINT<\/code>, <code>EXPOSE<\/code>, <code>VOLUME<\/code>, <code>ENV<\/code>, <code>ARG<\/code>, <code>WORKDIR<\/code>, <code>USER<\/code><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Understanding build context and caching<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Multi-stage builds for efficient image creation<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 5: Data Persistence in Docker<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Understanding data persistence challenges<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Using bind mounts and volumes<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The <code>VOLUME<\/code> instruction<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Best practices for managing persistent data<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 6: Container Lifecycle and Process Management<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Understanding <code>CMD<\/code> vs. <code>ENTRYPOINT<\/code><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Handling signals: SIGTERM and graceful shutdowns<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Container logs and troubleshooting<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n<!-- \/wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Day 2 \u2013 Advanced Docker &amp; Introduction to Kubernetes<\/strong><\/h2>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 7: Docker Image Management and Best Practices<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Committing changes with <code>docker commit<\/code><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Tagging images (<code>docker tag<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Using labels (<code>LABEL<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Optimizing images for size and performance<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Security best practices in Docker<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 8: The Docker Registry<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Understanding image registries (Docker Hub, Harbor)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Pushing and pulling images<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Setting up a private registry<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Registry best practices for security and efficiency<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 9: Working with Docker Compose<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Why use <code>docker-compose<\/code>?<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Writing <code>docker-compose.yml<\/code> files<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Managing multi-container applications<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Defining services, networks, and volumes<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Best practices for using Docker Compose<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 10: Introduction to Kubernetes<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What is Kubernetes?<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Kubernetes vs. Docker Swarm<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Key Kubernetes concepts (Pods, Deployments, Services)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Running containers in Kubernetes<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Next steps for learning Kubernetes<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n<!-- \/wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Hands-on Labs &amp; Final Project<\/strong><\/h2>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Lab 1<\/strong>: Building and running a custom Docker image<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Lab 2<\/stron